    Troubleshooting Notion errors
  </h1>

  <p class="mt-6 text-base text-gray-600 text-center">Updated: <time datetime="<%= item[:updated_at] %>"><%= item[:updated_at].strftime("%B %-d, %Y") %></time></p>

  <p class="mt-8">Below are some of the common issues with Notion and ways of fixing them.</p>

  <h2 class="my-8">Template duplication failed</h2>

  <img src="/assets/images/notion-template-duplication-failed-error.png" alt="Template duplication failed in Notion" class="shadow-lg rounded-lg my-8 mx-auto w-full md:w-3/5 border border-gray-200" loading="lazy">

  <p class="mt-8">It’s most likely a temporary glitch or a permissions problem inside the template’s nested pages (usually databases). Fixes:</p>

  <ul class="mt-8 text-xl text-gray-700 leading-8">
    <li class="mt-4">Try duplicating from the mobile app - it could bypass the issue.</li>
    <li class="mt-4">Check sharing on every page and database inside the template. If a sub-page has stricter permissions, duplication can fail even if the top page is shared. Explicitly share all nested pages/databases, not just the parent.</li>
    <li class="mt-4">If all else fails, wait a bit and try again - this is a known (temporary) issue on Notion’s side.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="my-8">Notion won’t load at all</h2>

  <p class="mt-8">If you can't load Notion from your browser, it could be a network/DNS issue or a glitch in the desktop app. Fixes:</p>

  <ul class="mt-8 text-xl text-gray-700 leading-8">
    <li class="mt-4">Switch your DNS to 8.8.8.8 (Google DNS) or 1.1.1.1 (Cloudflare). Some corporatenetworks block Notion at the DNS level.</li>
    <li class="mt-4">Desktop app → View → Force Reload. This clears cache without a full reinstall.</li>
    <li class="mt-4">If the web app loads but the desktop app doesn’t, reinstall the desktop app. (You won't lose your data)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="my-8">Export fails</h2>

  <p class="mt-8">Large or complex workspace exports can take time - up to several days. Fixes:</p>

  <ul class="mt-8 text-xl text-gray-700 leading-8">
    <li class="mt-4">Try again. For large exports, give it some time - Notion processes the export in the background.</li>
    <li class="mt-4">If the ZIP won’t open (on Windows), use <a href="https://7-zip.org" class="underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">7-Zip</a> to extract the backup.</li>
    <li class="mt-4">Expect layout quirks for PDF exports: page breaks, wide tables, toggles, code blocks, and embeds don’t always render cleanly. Inline images can shift; complex databases flatten.</li>
  </ul>

    <p class="mt-8">It is a good idea to make regular backups of your workspace to avoid losing your data.</p>

